          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_q1",
              "content": "Q: What's the performance overhead of inline filtering?",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 700,
                "font_size": 20,
                "color": "#4299e1",
                "margin_bottom": 12
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_a1",
              "content": "A: <100ms latency for most transformations. We use Bacalhau's WebAssembly runtime for near-native performance. Filters run in parallel, not serial. For 99.9% of workloads, overhead is negligible (<5%). High-throughput customers (>1M events/sec) run dedicated compute nodes.",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 400,
                "font_size": 16,
                "line_height": 1.6,
                "color": "#FFFFFF"
              },
              "emphasis": {
                "phrases": ["<100ms latency", "<5%", "near-native performance"],
                "color": "#48BB78",
                "font_weight": 600
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "technical_objection_row",
          "id": "tech_obj_2",
          "position": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 192,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 160
          },
          "style": {
            "background": "rgba(66, 153, 225, 0.08)",
            "border_left": "6px solid #fc8181",
            "border_radius": 8,
            "padding": 32
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_q2",
              "content": "Q: How do you handle schema evolution and breaking changes?",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 700,
                "font_size": 20,
                "color": "#4299e1",
                "margin_bottom": 12
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_a2",
              "content": "A: Policies are schema-aware but fault-tolerant. If a field doesn't exist, the filter passes data through unchanged (fail-open). You version policies in Git. We support gradual rollouts (canary deployments). Schema changes? Update your policy config—no code recompile needed.",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 400,
                "font_size": 16,
                "line_height": 1.6,
                "color": "#FFFFFF"
              },
              "emphasis": {
                "phrases": ["fail-open", "version policies in Git", "no code recompile"],
                "color": "#48BB78",
                "font_weight": 600
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "technical_objection_row",
          "id": "tech_obj_3",
          "position": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 384,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 160
          },
          "style": {
            "background": "rgba(66, 153, 225, 0.08)",
            "border_left": "6px solid #fc8181",
            "border_radius": 8,
            "padding": 32
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_q3",
              "content": "Q: What happens if the Expanso agent crashes or goes offline?",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 700,
                "font_size": 20,
                "color": "#4299e1",
                "margin_bottom": 12
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_a3",
              "content": "A: Data flows through unchanged—we're fail-safe by design. No agent = no filtering, but no data loss. Agents auto-restart on failure (systemd/k8s). You get alerting on agent health. For critical workloads, deploy agents in HA pairs with automatic failover.",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 400,
                "font_size": 16,
                "line_height": 1.6,
                "color": "#FFFFFF"
              },
              "emphasis": {
                "phrases": ["fail-safe by design", "no data loss", "HA pairs"],
                "color": "#48BB78",
                "font_weight": 600
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "technical_objection_row",
          "id": "tech_obj_4",
          "position": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 576,
            "width": 1760,
            "height": 160
          },
          "style": {
            "background": "rgba(66, 153, 225, 0.08)",
            "border_left": "6px solid #fc8181",
            "border_radius": 8,
            "padding": 32
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_q4",
              "content": "Q: Can we test this without disrupting production?",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 700,
                "font_size": 20,
                "color": "#4299e1",
                "margin_bottom": 12
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tech_a4",
              "content": "A: Yes—shadow mode. Agents tap data streams, apply filters, and report metrics WITHOUT actually dropping data. You see what would be filtered, but nothing changes in production. After validation, flip to active mode. Most teams shadow for 1-2 weeks before going live.",
              "style": {
                "font_family": "Inter",
                "font_weight": 400,
                "font_size": 16,
                "line_height": 1.6,
                "color": "#FFFFFF"
              },
              "emphasis": {
                "phrases": ["shadow mode", "WITHOUT actually dropping data", "1-2 weeks"],
                "color": "#48BB78",
                "font_weight": 600
              }
            }
          ]
        },
